Subject: Re: [T2] starting and warm up

On May 26, 2004, at 10:58 AM, Mark Hineline wrote:

> With all the Bosch Jetronics of the 1970s and early 80s, the way to go 
> is to turn the key to the start position for just an instant. Then 
> turn to the off position. Then back to start and let it crank. I was 
> taught this for Volvos -- the notion is that it "charges up" the fuel 
> ring -- and it works equally well with my bus (although the VW 
> starting circuit requires turning the key to the off position before 
> going back to start).

I have found that starting is easier this way, too.  I find that on a 
cold morning, if I crank for a few seconds and it almost catches, I 
turn the key off, crank it again, and it starts immediately.

I never touch the accelerator pedal when starting ... totally not 
necessary on FI.

